        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 3:24PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 324 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Grand Bay, moving southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Grand Bay, Bayou La Batre, and Coden.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
